author: COMSOL
description: A stent is a wire-mesh tube used to open a coronary artery during angioplasty, a process for the removal or compression of plaque. The expanded stent acts as a scaffold that keeps the blood vessel open. During this procedure, damage can be inflicted on the artery by both the nonuniform expansion of the stent, as well as by its foreshortening. This example studies the deformation of a stent subjected to a radial outward pressure using an elastoplastic material model with linear hardening.
